cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it discusses the use of simultaneous matrix diagonalization as a subroutine in many machine learning problems. The paper also introduces extensions to the perturbation analysis of these methods, which is relevant to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. The use of joint diagonalization in blind source separation and parameter estimation in latent variable models suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. Finally, the potential applications of joint diagonalization in computer vision problems suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
